        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down.</hi> | Beckenham | <hi rend="print">Kent. S.E.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Ap. 25<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I am pleased to hear about the new Edit. of Vol I.—<ref target="#foot.f2"/> I have directed M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Murray to send you immediately by Post clean sheets of the last Reprint.—<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p>
<p>I am very sorry that I cannot point out corrected passages; &amp; I must beg you to glance over all the pages. The corrections are not numerous, but a few are important.— I have been worked to death by letters &amp; the Reprints, &amp; this has prevented me keeping any account of corrections.—<ref target="#foot.f4"/></p>
<p>Very many thanks for your criticisms.— What I meant about the Neuroptera &amp; Orthoptera, <hi rend="underline">now quite distinct</hi>, I cannot conceive; I know that they were partially united by some of the best Entomologists; Pray correct sentence.—<ref target="#foot.f5"/></p>
<p>I do not know when my book on Expression will be published—<ref target="#foot.f6"/> I have written the first very rough copy of the whole;—but I intend to lay it on one side this summer for some months &amp; refresh myself with some simple Botanical work, &amp; complete some curious observations which I made some ten years ago on the extraordinary sensibility of certain plants to various stimuli.—<ref target="#foot.f7"/></p>
<p>I hope that you made a good bargain with the publisher, as I hope the book will sell well in Germany.— In England 6500 copies have been printed.— But the late war will no doubt interfere with sale.—<ref target="#foot.f8"/></p>
<p>In Haste | Yours very sincerely | Ch Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
